The appointment of [Greg Peters](/Greg_Peters_(businessman)) and [Ted Sarandos](/Ted_Sarandos) as co-CEOs in January 2023, with Hastings transitioning to executive chairman, marked a new leadership era. &#91;352&#93; &#91;353&#93; Peters's background as COO and Chief Product Officer, and Sarandos's role as Chief Content Officer, provided a solid foundation for this transition. &#91;354&#93; &#91;355&#93; The discontinuation of the [DVD-by-mail](/DVD-by-mail) service on September 29, 2023, after over 5 billion shipments, signified the end of an era and a definitive pivot to digital. &#91;356&#93; &#91;357&#93; &#91;358&#93; Promotions within the executive ranks, with Eunice Kim becoming Chief Product Officer and Elizabeth Stone Chief Technology Officer, &#91;359&#93; and a multi-film agreement with [Skydance Animation](/Skydance_Animation) starting with [Spellbound](/Spellbound_(2024_film)), &#91;360&#93; &#91;361&#93; signaled continued strategic development. The inaugural "What We Watched: A Netflix Engagement Report" provided unprecedented transparency into viewership data, &#91;362&#93; &#91;363&#93; revealing [The Night Agent](/The_Night_Agent) as the most-watched show globally for the first half of 2023. &#91;364&#93;

